long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86443 build.xml file that points to launcher contribution directories instead of launchertmp
Build ID: I20071213-1700
Steps To Reproduce: 1. Build an eclipse distribution, which requires re-compilation of libs as contributed binaries, from source (e.g., solaris-gtk-x86 or linux-gtk-s390) 2. There will be an error in the /features/org.eclipse.platform/build.xml task "rootFiles${os}_${ws}_${arch}" (e.g., rootFilessolaris_gtk_x68 or rootFileslinux_gtk_s390) because launchertmp is no longer used by the root build.xml script.
More information: The following tasks still expect their contributed launcher libraries to be in the ${basedir}/../../launchertmp directory: rootFileslinux_gtk_ppc64 rootFileslinux_gtk_s390 rootFilessolaris_gtk_x86 rootFileshpux_motif_ia64
Instead, these directories should be (respectively): ${basedir}/../../features/org.eclipse.equinox.executable/contributed/gtk/linux/ppc64 ${basedir}/../../features/org.eclipse.equinox.executable/contributed/gtk/linux/s390 ${basedir}/../../features/org.eclipse.equinox.executable/contributed/gtk/solaris/x86 ${basedir}/../../features/org.eclipse.equinox.executable/contributed/motif/hpux/ia64
(see the /build_base/build.xml file, line 103 for the change from launchertmp to these contributed directories between 3.3.0 and 3.4M4).
I will also attach a modified version of /features/org.eclipse.platform/build.xml taht makes these changes (since I do not have contributor permission and could not find this build script in the CVS repository).

Created attachment 86482 patch
The linux gtk ppc64 and hpux motif ia64 libs don't have people lined up to contribute them, this is the reason there aren't directories in the equinox executable feature.

Thanks, Kim. True enough. Should a similar directory structure with a readme.txt placeholder (similar to what is currently in /features/org.eclipse.equinox.executable/contributed/gtk/solaris/x86) be put in place for linux gtk ppc64 and hpux motif ia64, then? I guess the point of the bug is more that the launchertmp directory no longer seems to be used by the /<build_base>/build.xml. If I have misunderstood, please clarify. Thanks! -Tim.
I was actually going to remove support for linux gtk ppc64 and hpux motif ia64. These haven't been contributed to or used in years.
Created attachment 86574 patch to remove references to linux gtk ppc64 and hpux motif ia64
